Subject: Repository: Submission â€“ Registry checks complete ({0}, {1})

<div style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;">
    <div style="width: 100%; border: 1px solid #000000; margin-bottom: 25px!important; padding: 2px!important; text-align: center;">This is a notification email for information only and <strong>no action is required.</strong></div>
    <p style="padding-bottom: 15px;">Dear {0},</p>
    <p>Thank you again for completing your thesis submission into the St Andrews Research Repository.</p>
    <p style="padding-bottom: 15px;">This email is to let you know that the first set of checks have now been completed by the Registry Student Office (Postgraduates).</p>
    <p><strong>What happens next?</strong></p>
    <p>The Library E-theses team will now begin their checking process on your submission. Their checks will focus on ensuring that all necessary files and correct versions have been submitted.</p>
    <p style="padding-bottom: 15px;">The E-theses team may need you to upload more information or files, or they may have other questions for you. If they do, they will send you an email to request this information.</p>
    <p style="padding-bottom: 15px;">If you need to contact the E-theses team at any point during their checks, their email address is <a href="mailto:digirep@st-andrews.ac.uk">digirep@st-andrews.ac.uk</a>.</p>
    <p>Once the E-theses team have completed their checks they will make your submission publicly available in the repository, (subject to the terms of any embargo), and you will receive two emails to confirm this.</p>
    <p style="padding-bottom: 15px;">(The first email will be an acknowledgement email generated by the Repository, followed by an email from the E-theses team which will contain the DOI assigned to your thesis).</p>
    <p style="padding-bottom: 15px;">If you are asked to log in to the Repository again then you will need to revisit your Submissions Page. However, precise instructions and links will be given in any emails you receive from Registry or the Library.</p>
    <p>Registry Student Office (Postgraduates)</p>
    <p>St Andrews Research Repository E-theses Team</p>
</div>
